value.value: A stalk (PO:0009025) of a leaflet (PO:0020049).
Stipule-like appendage(s) at the base of a leaflet (in unifoliolate or simple leaves, found at the top of the petiole).
A scale leaf that surrounds a dormant or perennating bud.
A stalk (PO:0025066) that is the main axis of a pinnate or more highly compound leaf, that bears leaflets or divisions of the axis.
That part of the seed coat that develops from the inner integument.
That part of the seed coat that develops from the outer integument, or from the single integument when there is only one.
A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) which is diploid nutritive tissue in an angiosperm seed derived from nucellar tissue.
An arilloid that is an outgrowth of a seed next to the micropyle.

definition.value: Often hard and generally smaller and less elaborate than a arillode.

value.value: A portion of seed coat epidermis (PO:0006048) that consists of multiple seed trichomes (PO:0004511) at the seed micropyle (PO:0006334).
A cardinal organ part that is an oil-secreting outgrowth of a seed or fruit.

definition.value: May be a modified arilloid (a type of strophiole or caruncle) or may be an outgrowth of a fruit. May be attractive to ants and aid in dispersal.

value.value: A cardinal part of multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025498) that is a scar on a seed (PO:0009010) at the place where it was attached to a funicle (PO:0020006).
A cardinal part of multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025498) which is one carpellate unit of a schizocarp fruit (PO:0030098) consisting of pericarp (PO:0009084) and one or more seeds (PO:0009010).

definition.value: A mericarp develops from one carpel of a syncarpous gynoecium. The pericarp of each carpel are fused together until maturity, at which point the carpellate units separate from one another.

value.value: An embryo sac cell (PO:0025026) that is largest cell in a mature embryo sac (PO:0025074).

definition.value: In most angiosperms, the embryo sac central cell contains two polar nuclei, and, after double fertilization, develops into an endosperm. In some angiosperms, such as Illicium, the embryo sac central cell contains a single polar nucleus. Embryo sac central cell is distinct from archegonium central cell (PO:0025509).

value.value: Cell, commonly three in number as in the eight-nucleate embryo sac, located at the other end of the embryo sac from the egg cell.

definition.value: More or less persistent, multiplicative or not.

value.value: A gamete (PO:0025006) produced by an archegonium (PO:0025126) or an embryo sac (PO:0025074).

definition.value: The plant egg cell (megagamete) is usually larger than the plant sperm cell (PO:0000084; microgamete).

value.value: A cardinal organ part that has as parts an egg cell and two synergids and is located at the micropylar end of the embryo sac.

definition.value: Found in angiosperms.

value.value: A spermatogenous cell (PO:0025525) of the microgametophyte (PO:0025280) that divides to produce two pollen sperm cells (PO:0025121).

definition.value: Occurs in angiosperms.

value.value: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that is the larger cell of a microgametophyte (PO:0025280) in seed plants. It does not divide further and develops into a pollen tube cell (PO:0025195).
A stem internode (PO:0020142) below the cotyledonary node (PO:0025321) and transitional to a root (PO:0009005) of a plant embryo (PO:0009009) or a seedling (PO:0000003).
A plant anatomical space that is a slit in an anther lobe formed from when a dehiscence zone dehisces.

definition.value: Pollen may be released through the stomium. If you are annotating to this structure for Zea mays or other grasses, please also add an annotation to the corresponding floret type. Choose the most specific term possible from: spikelet floret (PO:0009082), tassel floret (PO:0006310), lower floret of pedicellate spikelet of tassel (PO:0006313), lower floret of sessile spikelet of tassel (PO:0006315), upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of tassel (PO:0006314), upper floret of sessile spikelet of tassel (PO:0006316).

value.value: A portion of ground tissue (PO:0025059) in the style of a carpel through which a pollen tube grows; it connects a stigma and the inside of an ovary.

definition.value: If you are annotating to this structure for Zea mays or other grasses, please also add an annotation to the corresponding floret type. Choose the most specific term possible from: spikelet floret (PO:0009082), ear floret (PO:0006354), upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear (PO:0006350), upper floret of sessile spikelet of ear (PO:0006352).

value.value: The last mature leaf before the inflorescence in a cereal crop plant.
A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) that is the lower part of a vascular leaf (PO:0009025), and which more or less encases the stem (PO:0009047).

definition.value: A leaf sheath is usually tubular shaped, and is found in the Poaceae family and other monocots.

value.value: A membranous or hairy appendage on the adaxial/upper surface of a leaf, at the junction between sheath and blade, especially in grasses.
A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) that is an ear-shaped outgrowth of the distal part of a leaf sheath (PO:0020104).

definition.value: May wrap around the stem (PO:0009047) or branch (PO:0025073) to which the vascular leaf (PO:0009025) it is part of is attached. Found in some Poaceae.

value.value: An embryonic plant structure at the base of a plant embryo that develops from an embryonic basal cell and connects an embryo proper to the wall of a megagametophyte.

definition.value: The suspensor often allows the embryo to penetrate deep into the endosperm. Across plant species, suspensors are morphologically diverse and may be single- or multicellular, undifferentiated or highly differentiated, and variously shaped.

value.value: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that is the uppermost cell of a suspensor (PO:0020108) and from which part of the root (PO:0009005) and root cap (PO:0020123) in a plant embryo (PO:0009009) of angiosperms are derived.
An embryonic plant structure that is a more or less shield-shaped and absorptive portion of a plant embryo of Poaceae.

definition.value: May be a modified cotyledon.

value.value: A root (PO:0009005) that develops from a lateral root primordium (PO:0000016) that is part of another root on the same plant.

definition.value: A lateral root primordium may develops on any root, including a primary root (PO:0020127), on an existing lateral root (PO:0020121), or a shoot-borne root (PO:0000042). In seed plants, a lateral root primordium generally develops from pericycle cells (PO:0025261), but cells of an endodermis (PO:0000252) may also participate in its formation in some species. In ferns, lateral root primordia develop from the endodermis.

value.value: A shoot axis (PO:0025029) that is part of an inflorescence (PO:0009049).

definition.value: An inflorescence axis (PO:0020122) has either a determinate apex, which terminates in a flower meristem (PO:0000229), or has an indeterminate apex, which terminates in an inflorescence apical meristem (PO:0009108).  An inflorescence pedicel (PO:0009052) is the simplest example of a determinate inflorescence axis.

value.value: A portion of root parenchyma (PO:0025095) tissue that is part of the root tip (PO:0000025) and covers the root apical meristem (PO:0020147).

definition.value: Often composed of living and dead parenchyma cells. Protects the root apical meristem.

value.value: A stele (PO:0025197) that is part of a root (PO:0009005).

definition.value: Includes the pericycle as the outermost layer of the stele.

value.value: A staminate inflorescence (PO:0025601) in Zea species that bears the tassel spikelet (PO:0006309) on a terminal inflorescence axis (PO:0020122).

definition.value: Branched inflorescence with a central axis and about 10-50 lateral branches.

value.value: A root (PO:0009005) that develops directly from a seedling radicle (PO:0020127).

definition.value: The first root of a plant.  In dicots and gymnosperms  it becomes the tap root, the central axis of a root system (PO:0025025).

value.value: A phyllome margin (PO:0025018) that is part of a leaf (PO:0025034).

definition.value: If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025) or non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075), depending on the species. All annotations for angiosperms, gymnosperms, and pteridophytes should go to vascular leaf and all annotations for bryophytes should go to non-vascular leaf.

value.value: A portion of root parenchyma tissue that is the central part of a root cap in which the cells are arranged in longitudinal files.
A portion of root parenchyma tissue that is part of a root cap and is parallel to the sides of a root axis.

definition.value: This is the general term for the lateral portion of any root cap and not the term for a root cap of lateral root (PO:0003018) or lateral root cap of lateral root (PO:0003020).

value.value: Cell that constitutes the central part of the root cap, arranged in longitudinal files.
A root initial cell (PO:0000059) that produces columella cells in the root cap (PO:0020123). In direct contact with quiescent center (PO:0020149).
A plant axis differentiation zone that is the part of a root and is located behind a root elongation zone.

definition.value: Most of the primary tissues of a root mature in the differentiation zone. This zone is where root hairs are produced.

value.value: A pistillate inflorescence (PO:0025598) in Zea species that is highly compacted and bears the ear spikelets (PO:0006320) on a lateral inflorescence axis (PO:0020122).
A phyllome apex (PO:0025139) that is part of a leaf (PO:0025034).

definition.value: It is not precisely defined how far toward the base from the tip a leaf apex extends. For the apical most portion of a leaf, use the term leaf tip. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025) or non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075), depending on the species. All annotations for angiosperms, gymnosperms, and pteridophytes should go to vascular leaf and all annotations for bryophytes should go to non-vascular leaf.

value.value: A phyllome lamina vein (PO:0025348) that is part of a leaf lamina vascular system (PO:0000048).
A primary leaf vein (PO:0025413) that is the central vein of a vascular leaf (PO:0009025).

definition.value: Often the most prominent vein of a vascular leaf. See costa (PO:0030072) for the central conductive strand of a non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075).

value.value: A leaf lamina vein (PO:0020138) arising from a primary leaf vein (PO:0025413).

definition.value: Vein orders only apply to hierarchically branching vein patterns, not to dichotomously branching vein patterns, as found in some ferns and gymnosperms.

value.value: A shoot axis node (PO:0005004) that is part of a stem (PO:0009047).
A shoot axis internode (PO:0005005) that is part of a stem (PO:0009047).

definition.value: See node.

value.value: A maximal portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) located at a shoot apex (PO:0000037) or root tip (PO:0000025).
A portion of meristem (PO:0009013) tissue located parallel to the sides of a shoot axis (PO:0025029) or root (PO:0009005) that participates in lateral growth.

definition.value: A term for lateral growth has been requested in GO. Lateral meristems contribute to an increase in the cross-sectional area of a shoot axis or root. Examples of lateral meristems are: cambium (PO:0005597) (includes cork cambium (PO:0005599) and vascular cambium (PO:0005598)), shoot lateral meristem (PO:0006344) (includes primary thickening meristem (PO:0005039)), root lateral meristem (PO:0006308), and secondary thickening meristem (PO:0025414). Contrasts with apical meristem (PO:0020144), phyllome marginal meristem (PO:0025404), or intercalary meristem (PO:0006073).

value.value: A root meristem (PO:0006085) located at the root tip (PO:0000025), behind the root cap (PO:0020123).

definition.value: In most cases, it is involved in root elongation.
